# TFM macOS signing configuration (template).
#
# Copy this file to `signing.env` (which is gitignored) and fill in your values:
#
#     cp signing.env.example signing.env
#
# build.sh and create_dmg.sh source signing.env automatically, so you don't have
# to re-export these every session. Anything already set in the environment
# overrides what's here.
#
# NOTE: Neither value is a secret. CODESIGN_IDENTITY is only the certificate's
# display name (the private key stays in your keychain), and NOTARY_PROFILE is
# only the name of a notarytool keychain profile (the app-specific password was
# stored encrypted in the keychain by `xcrun notarytool store-credentials`).
# signing.env is gitignored anyway so per-machine values never get committed.

# The "Developer ID Application" identity used to sign the app and DMG.
# Find yours with: security find-identity -v -p codesigning
CODESIGN_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Your Name (TEAMID)"

# The notarytool keychain profile used to notarize + staple. Create it once with:
#   xcrun notarytool store-credentials "TFM-Notary" \
#       --apple-id you@example.com --team-id TEAMID --password <app-specific-pw>
# Leave unset/empty to sign but not notarize.
NOTARY_PROFILE="TFM-Notary"
